2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE BILL NO. 151
BY SENATOR MIZELL AND REPRESENTATIVES MANDIE LANDRY AND SPELL
1 AN ACT
2 To enact R.S. 15:609(K), relative to drawing or taking of DNA samples; to provide for rules
3 to flag a driver's license for certain persons under certain circumstances; and to
4 provide for related matters.
5 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
6 Section 1. R.S. 15:609(K) is hereby enacted to read as follows:
7 §609. Drawing or taking of DNA samples
8 * * *
9 K. (1)Any person required by law to submit a DNA sample and who has
10 failed to provide that sample, shall be considered noncompliant.
11 (2) Upon notification of noncompliance by the appropriate agency, the
12 office of motor vehicles shall place a flag on the person's driving record. The
13 office of motor vehicles shall not issue, renew, or reinstate any driver's license
14 for the person until proof of compliance with the DNA submission requirement
15 has been received.
16 (3) No later than January 1, 2027, the state police shall promulgate rules
17 to flag a driver's license for outstanding Combined DNA Index System (CODIS)
18 hits and persons that lawfully owe the state a DNA sample in order to complete
19 their full DNA profile.
